R O Y   H A R P E R
1971 - Stormcock

If you like Progressive Folk (esp. Jethro Tull) you shouldn't miss this album. Released in 1971 it obviously has been a big inspiration for Ian Anderson resp. Tull's &quot;Thick as a Brick&quot; that came out one year later. Roy Harper has earned great reputation among rock bands like Led Zeppelin (&quot;Hats Off to Roy Harper&quot;) or Pink Floyd who let him do the lead vocals on &quot;Have a Cigar&quot;.

